{
    "level": "A1–A2",
    "intro": "In this topic you will learn <strong>three articles</strong> of the English language: <strong>a</strong>, <strong>an</strong> and <strong>the</strong> - when to use them and when to do without them.",
    "rules": [
        {
            "label": "A / An",
            "color": "emerald",
            "text": "<strong>Indefinite article</strong> - something general or new:",
            "example": "I saw a dog. / She is an engineer."
        },
        {
            "label": "The",
            "color": "blue",
            "text": "<strong>Definite article</strong> is something specific or known:",
            "example": "The dog was big. / The sun is bright."
        },
        {
            "label": "Zero (Ø)",
            "color": "amber",
            "text": "<strong>No article</strong> - general concepts, plural:",
            "example": "I love music. / Dogs are loyal."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "1. Three types of articles",
    "intro": "In the English language, there are three ways to use articles:",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "A / An",
            "title": "Indefinite",
            "subtitle": "Indefinite article — something new or general (a book, an apple)"
        },
        {
            "label": "The",
            "title": "Definite",
            "subtitle": "Definite article — something specific or known (the book I bought)"
        },
        {
            "label": "Zero Ø",
            "title": "No article",
            "subtitle": "Zero article — abstract concepts, general plural (I love music)"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "2. A vs An - when which?",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "A - before a consonant SOUND",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "The article <strong>a</strong> is used before words that <strong>begin with a consonant sound</strong>.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "a book, a car, a dog",
                    "ua": "book, car, dog"
                },
                {
                    "en": "a university [juːnɪˈvɜːsɪti]",
                    "ua": "a university (the [j] sound is a consonant!)"
                },
                {
                    "en": "a European country",
                    "ua": "a European country (the [j] sound)"
                },
                {
                    "en": "a one-way street",
                    "ua": "a one-way street (sound (w)) idea"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "An — перед голосним ЗВУКОМ",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "Артикль <strong>an</strong> вживається перед словами, що <strong>починаються з голосного звуку</strong>.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "an apple, an egg, an idea",
                    "ua": "яблуко, яйце, ідея"
                },
                {
                    "en": "an hour [aʊə]",
                    "ua": "an hour (h is silent, sound [aʊ] is loud!)"
                },
                {
                    "en": "an honest person",
                    "ua": "an honest person (h is silent)"
                },
                {
                    "en": "an MBA degree",
                    "ua": "an MBA degree (sound [e] - vowel)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Important!",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "Choosing a/an depends on the <strong>SOUND</strong>, not the letter!",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "a uniform (sound [j])",
                    "ua": "uniform"
                },
                {
                    "en": "an umbrella (sound [ʌ])",
                    "ua": "umbrella"
                }
            ],
            "note": "📌 Look at pronunciation, not spelling!"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "3. When to use A / An (unspecified)",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Something new / for the first time",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "When we <strong>first mention</strong> something or <strong>do not specify</strong> what exactly.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "I saw a cat in the garden.",
                    "ua": "I saw a cat in the garden. (some unknown)"
                },
                {
                    "en": "She bought a new dress.",
                    "ua": "She bought a new dress."
                },
                {
                    "en": "There is a problem.",
                    "ua": "There is a problem. (some)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Professions and roles",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "When we talk about <strong>profession, nationality, religion</strong>.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "She is a doctor.",
                    "ua": "She is a doctor."
                },
                {
                    "en": "He is an engineer.",
                    "ua": "He engineer."
                },
                {
                    "en": "I'm a student.",
                    "ua": "I'm a student."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "One of many",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "When we mean <strong>one representative of a group</strong>.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "A dog is a loyal animal.",
                    "ua": "A dog is a loyal animal. (any dog)"
                },
                {
                    "en": "I need a pen.",
                    "ua": "I need a pen. (any)"
                }
            ],
            "note": "A/An = "one", "some", "any"."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "4. When to use THE (designated)",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Already known / mentioned",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "When the interlocutor <strong>knows</strong> what is being said, or it has already been <strong>mentioned</strong>.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "I saw a cat. The cat was black.",
                    "ua": "I saw a cat. The cat was black."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Where is the bathroom?",
                    "ua": "Where is the bathroom? (in this house)"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Did you read the book I gave you?",
                    "ua": "Did you read the book I gave you?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "One of a kind",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "When something is <strong>unique</strong> or <strong>one of a kind</strong>.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "the sun, the moon, the Earth",
                    "ua": "sun, moon, Earth"
                },
                {
                    "en": "the Internet, the radio",
                    "ua": "інтернет, радіо"
                },
                {
                    "en": "the President of Ukraine",
                    "ua": "Президент України"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "З визначенням / уточненням",
            "color": "purple",
            "description": "Коли є <strong>уточнення</strong> (of, that, which, тощо).",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "the capital of France",
                    "ua": "столиця Франції"
                },
                {
                    "en": "the man in the red jacket",
                    "ua": "чоловік у червоній куртці"
                },
                {
                    "en": "the book that you recommended",
                    "ua": "книга, яку ти порекомендував"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Geography and places",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "With some geographical names:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "the USA, the UK, the Netherlands",
                    "ua": "USA, Great Britain, the Netherlands"
                },
                {
                    "en": "the Pacific Ocean, the Dnipro",
                    "ua": "Pacific ocean, Dnipro"
                },
                {
                    "en": "the Alps, the Carpathians",
                    "ua": "Alps, Karpaty"
                }
            ],
            "note": "The = "the same", "specific", "known"."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "5. When NOT to use the article (Zero Article)",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "General concepts / abstractions",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "When we talk about something <strong>in general</strong>, abstract concepts.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "I love music.",
                    "ua": "I love music. (music in general)"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Life is beautiful.",
                    "ua": "Life is beautiful."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Money is not everything.",
                    "ua": "Money is not everything.[[[CODX_30]]]Plurality in general"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Множина в загальному",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "When we talk about <strong>plurality in general</strong>.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Dogs are loyal animals.",
                    "ua": "Dogs are loyal animals. (all dogs)"
                },
                {
                    "en": "I like cats.",
                    "ua": "I like cats. (cats in general)"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Books are expensive.",
                    "ua": "Books are expensive."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Countries, cities, names",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "Most <strong>proper names</strong> do not need an article.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Ukraine, Kyiv, London",
                    "ua": "Ukraine, Kyiv, London"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Mount Everest, Lake Baikal",
                    "ua": "Mount Everest, Lake Baikal"
                },
                {
                    "en": "John, Maria",
                    "ua": "John, Maria"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Stable expressions",
            "color": "purple",
            "description": "In many <strong>regular expressions</strong> have no article.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "at home, at work, at school",
                    "ua": "at home, at work, at school"
                },
                {
                    "en": "by bus, by car, by plane",
                    "ua": "by bus, by car, by plane"
                },
                {
                    "en": "go to bed, have breakfast",
                    "ua": "go to bed, have breakfast"
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "6. Comparison table",
    "intro": "Main cases of article use:",
    "rows": [
        {
            "en": "First mention",
            "ua": "First mention",
            "note": "A/An: I saw a dog."
        },
        {
            "en": "Known / mentioned",
            "ua": "Known / mentioned mentioned",
            "note": "The: The dog was big."
        },
        {
            "en": "Unique things",
            "ua": "Unique things",
            "note": "The: the sun, the moon"
        },
        {
            "en": "Professions",
            "ua": "Professions",
            "note": "A/An: She is a teacher."
        },
        {
            "en": "General / abstract",
            "ua": "General / abstract",
            "note": "Ø: I love music."
        },
        {
            "en": "Plural in general",
            "ua": "Plural in general",
            "note": "Ø: Dogs are loyal."
        }
    ],
    "warning": "📌 <strong>A/An</strong> = new, one of many. <strong>The</strong> = specific, known. <strong>Ø</strong> = general concept."
}

{
    "title": "7. Special cases",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "The + adjective = group of people",
            "color": "purple",
            "description": "<strong>The + adjective</strong> means a group of people.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "the rich, the poor",
                    "ua": "rich, poor (people)"
                },
                {
                    "en": "the young, the elderly",
                    "ua": "youth, people elderly"
                },
                {
                    "en": "the unemployed",
                    "ua": "unemployed"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Musical instruments",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "With musical instruments we use <strong>the</strong>.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "play the piano",
                    "ua": " piano"
                },
                {
                    "en": "play the guitar",
                    "ua": "play the guitar"
                },
                {
                    "en": "play the violin",
                    "ua": "play the violin"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Time of day",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "With the time of day: <strong>in the morning/afternoon/evening</strong>, but At night</strong>. Typical mistakes of Ukrainian speakers",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "in the morning",
                    "ua": "вранці"
                },
                {
                    "en": "in the afternoon",
                    "ua": "вдень"
                },
                {
                    "en": "at night (без the!)",
                    "ua": "вночі"
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "8. Типові помилки україномовних",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Error 1",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Omission of the article before the profession.",
            "wrong": "She is doctor.",
            "right": "​​​​ <span class="font-mono">She is a doctor.</span>"
        },
        {
            "label": "Error 2",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "A instead of An before a vowel sound.",
            "wrong": "a hour, an honest person",
            "right": "​​​​​​​​"
        },
        {
            "label": "Помилка 3",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "The with abstract concepts.",
            "wrong": "The life is beautiful.",
            "right": "​​​​​​​​​​ Ukraine."
        },
        {
            "label": "Помилка 4",
            "color": "purple",
            "title": "Артикль перед країнами (більшість).",
            "wrong": "I live in the Ukraine.",
            "right": " ✅ <span class="font-mono">I live in Ukraine.</span>"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "10. Practice",
    "select_title": "Exercise 1. Choose the correct article",
    "select_intro": "Fill in the blanks with the article a, an, the or Ø (without an article).",
    "selects": [
        {
            "label": "She is ___ engineer. (a / an / the / Ø)",
            "prompt": "Which article?"
        },
        {
            "label": "I saw ___ sun today. (a / an / the / Ø)",
            "prompt": "Which article?"
        },
        {
            "label": "___ dogs are loyal animals. (a / an / the / Ø)",
            "prompt": "Which article?"
        },
        {
            "label": "I need ___ hour to finish. (a / an / the / Ø)",
            "prompt": "Which article?"
        }
    ],
    "options": [
        "a",
        "an",
        "the",
        "Ø"
    ],
    "input_title": "Exercise 2. Choose a or an",
    "input_intro": "Write a or an before the word.",
    "inputs": [
        {
            "before": "___ university",
            "after": "→"
        },
        {
            "before": "___ honest answer",
            "after": "→"
        },
        {
            "before": "___ European country",
            "after": "→"
        }
    ],
    "rephrase_title": "Exercise 3. Correct the error",
    "rephrase_intro": "Find and correct the error with the article.",
    "rephrase": [
        {
            "example_label": "Example:",
            "example_original": "He is a teacher.",
            "example_target": "He is a teacher."
        },
        {
            "original": "1. I love the music.",
            "placeholder": "Fix the error"
        },
        {
            "original": "2. She lives in France. / Any — Quantity",
            "placeholder": "Виправ помилку"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "Інші сторінки з категорії Іменники, артиклі та кількість",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Articles A / An / The — Артиклі (поточна)",
            "current": true
        },
        {
            "label": "Countable vs Uncountable — Злічувані / незлічувані",
            "current": false
        },
        {
            "label": "Some / Any — Кількість",
            "current": false
        },
        {
            "label": "Much / Many / A lot of",
            "current": false
        }
    ]
}
